<paragraph blockId="30.[264,875,603,665]" box="[264,402,639,665]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<figureCitation box="[264,402,639,665]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 31" captionStart-1="FIGURE 32" captionStartId-0="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionStartId-1="68.[264,367,1147,1171]" captionTargetBox-0="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetBox-1="[272,1316,322,1126]" captionTargetId-0="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetId-1="figure-29@68.[271,1316,322,1126]" captionTargetPageId-0="67" captionTargetPageId-1="68" captionText-0="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 32. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Wings (holotype): A—forewing; B—hindwing." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028169" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5028169/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs. 31–32</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[264,1325,719,1705]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prather Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2004" box="[264,522,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Calamoceratidae" genus="Banyallarga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanchezi">
<emphasis box="[264,522,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Banyallarga sanchezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from all other species in the genus by the highly modified tergum X and the mesoventral process of the inferior appendage (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 31A</figureCitation>
). Tergum X has two pairs of long digitate ventrolateral processes. In addition, this is the only species in the genus that bears a long digitate mesal process on the coxopodite. The species is known only from a single male specimen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[264,1325,719,1705]" box="[312,777,919,945]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Adult. Forewing length 
<quantity box="[594,697,919,945]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.13" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="11.3">11.3 mm</quantity>
(n=1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[264,1325,719,1705]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Head golden brown. Maxillary palps golden brown. Antenna chestnut brown, each flagellomere pale basally. Dorsal pterothorax golden brown; ventrolateral thorax and legs golden brown, metathoracic tibia of male with long posterior setal fringe. Forewing mottled gold and golden brown. Hind wing of male with basal semimembranous sleeve or pouch, enclosing brush of long setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[264,1325,719,1705]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Male. Sternum VII with pointed anteromesal process. Tergum IX with anterior margin deeply emarginate; sternum IX strongly angularly projected posteriorly; pleural setae numerous (
<figureCitation box="[400,512,1239,1265]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 31B</figureCitation>
). Preanal appendage shorter than tergum X, narrow, apex slightly flexible, covered with long fine setae. Segment X with short spinelike setae along posterior midline; with two pairs of long digitate ventrolateral processes (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1213,1319,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 31B</figureCitation>
) Inferior appendage with long setae ventrally and laterally on coxopodite, base of coxopodite with long digitate mesal process; harpago of uniform diameter along length, with fine setae basally and peglike setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[673,780,1439,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 31B</figureCitation>
). Phallus with U­shaped phallotremal sclerite, thornlike setae on endothecal membrane (
<figureCitation box="[754,864,1479,1505]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[264,367,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[273,1308,317,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-36@67.[272,1309,316,1803]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. Banyallarga (Histricoverpa) sanchezi. Male (holotype): A—lateral view; B—dorsal view; C—inferior appendage, ventral view; D—phallus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5028165/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 31D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[264,1325,719,1705]" box="[312,536,1519,1545]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
